parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coleman Caravan Travel Trailer Floor Rot and Water Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The floor rot and water damage in Coleman Caravan travel trailers can cause structural instability, making it difficult to tow and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, the water damage can lead to mold growth, posing health risks to occupants.
symptoms: Spongy or soft floor
water flooding from the bathroom area
floor feels like it will collapse
musty or moldy odor inside the camper.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coleman Caravan Refrigerator Defrosting and Ammonia Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The refrigerator defrosting and ammonia leak in Coleman Caravan travel trailers can cause a fire hazard, posing a risk to occupants and nearby structures.
symptoms: Strong ammonia smell inside and outside the camper
yellow substance leaking from the rear panel
refrigerator not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coleman Caravan General Construction and Quality Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor construction and quality issues in Coleman Caravan travel trailers can lead to various safety hazards, including structural instability, water damage, and fire risks.
symptoms: Flooding
water damage
floor rot
spongy or soft floor
musty or moldy odor
refrigerator and microwave malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear of Brake Rotors and Pads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of brake rotors and pads can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noises when applying the brakes
vibration or pulsation when applying the brakes
uneven brake pad wear
excessive brake dust
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly inspect and diagnose brake problems can lead to delayed repairs, increased costs, and potentially cause accidents due to reduced braking performance.
symptoms: Dealer or technician fails to identify brake problems
brake problems are misdiagnosed
brake repairs are delayed or ignored
warranty claims are denied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the recreational vehicle microwave can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the users, potentially leading to food spoilage and safety hazards.
symptoms: The microwave does not heat food properly
the microwave turns off unexpectedly
the microwave displays an error code
the microwave has a burning smell
the microwave is not functioning at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed acceleration and high RPM can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lag when accelerating, which can lead to accidents or make it difficult to merge onto highways or navigate heavy traffic.
symptoms: The gas pedal has to be almost pressed to the floor before the vehicle accelerates
high RPM (around 3000) when accelerating
hesitation or lag when accelerating
difficulty merging onto highways or navigating heavy traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected release of the seat belt can lead to occupant ejection, increased risk of injury, or even fatalities, especially in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belt releases unexpectedly
the passenger is tossed out of their seat
the seat belt fails to restrain the occupant during a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty rear seat belt can fail to restrain occupants, leading to increased risk of injury or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The rear seat belt does not function properly
the rear seat belt releases unexpectedly
the rear seat belt fails to restrain the occupant during a crash.
